Correct Execution Order:
1. Capture the current window (parent)

String parentWindow = driver.getWindowHandle();
This gives the ID of the window where Selenium is currently working.

2. Perform the action that opens a new window

driver.findElement(By.id("openWindow")).click();
At this moment the child window opens.

3. Get all window handles
Now Selenium can see both windows.

Set<String> allWindows = driver.getWindowHandles();

Example internally:
[CDwindow-A1, CDwindow-B2]
Window	ID
Parent	CDwindow-A1
Child	CDwindow-B2

4. Switch to the child window
for(String window : allWindows){

    if(!window.equals(parentWindow)){
        driver.switchTo().window(window);
        break;
    }
}

Now Selenium control moves to: CDwindow-B2
From here onward, all actions happen in the child window.
Example:
driver.getTitle();
driver.findElement(...).click();

5. Switch back to the parent window, After finishing work in the child window:

driver.switchTo().window(parentWindow);
Now Selenium control returns to the original window.